Section 1:
1 L.D. 1672
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1107, L.D. 1672, “An Act to Allow
10 Participation in the Adult Use Cannabis Tracking System to Be Voluntary”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Provide for an Alternate Method for Tracking Adult Use Cannabis'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 28-B MRSA §105, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
16 3. Rules; alternate tracking method. Notwithstanding subsection 2, the office shall
17 adopt rules regarding an alternate tracking method that may be used by licensees as an
18 alternative to the tracking system implemented and administered by the office pursuant to
19 this section. The rules must provide for an alternate method for tracking adult use cannabis
20 and adult use cannabis products that will ensure the office's ability to implement a recall of
21 the licensee's adult use cannabis or adult use cannabis products. The rules for the alternate
22 tracking method may not include any requirements that would involve the licensee having
23 to purchase tags, labels or similar items for the purpose of tracking adult use cannabis or
24 adult use cannabis products. Rules adopted by the office pursuant to this subsection are
25 major substantive rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
26 Sec. 2. Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
27 Cannabis Policy; alternate tracking method rulemaking. In accordance with the
28 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 28-B, section 105, subsection 3, the Department of
29 Administrative and Financial Services, Office of Cannabis Policy shall, on or before
30 January 9, 2026, provisionally adopt and submit for legislative review rules necessary to
31 implement the alternate tracking method for adult use cannabis and adult use cannabis
32 products to be used by licensees as an alternative to the tracking system implemented and
33 administered by the office in accordance with Title 28-B, section 105. Rules adopted by
34 the office pursuant to this section are major substantive rules as defined in Title 5, chapter
35 375, subchapter 2-A.
