30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment requires the
3344 Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of Cannabis Policy, on or
3355 before January 9, 2026, to provisionally adopt and submit for legislative review major
3366 substantive rules necessary to adopt an alternate tracking method that may be used by adult
3377 use cannabis licensees as an alternative to the tracking system implemented and
3388 administered by the office. The rules must provide for an alternate method for tracking
3399 adult use cannabis and adult use cannabis products that will ensure the office's ability to
4400 implement a recall of the licensee's adult use cannabis or adult use cannabis products and
4411 may not include any requirements that would involve the licensee having to purchase tags,
Page 2 - 132LR1757(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1107, L.D. 1672
412 labels or similar items for the purpose of tracking adult use cannabis or adult use cannabis
423 products. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
